Capitals Defeat Rangers 2-1 in Overtime in Opening Game in NHL Playoffs

-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 
2011-04-14T02:56:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/capitals-defeat-rangers-2-1-in-overtime-in-opening-game-in-nhl-playoffs.html
The  New York Rangers  opened the
National Hockey League playoffs with an overtime loss, falling
to the Washington Capitals 2-1 tonight at the Verizon Center in
Washington.  Alexander Semin scored on a point-blank shot with 1:36 left
in overtime to give the Capitals the win.  After two scoreless periods, Matt Gilroy scored early in
the third period for the Rangers.  Alex Ovechkin  tied the game
for the Capitals with 6:16 left in regulation on a goal that was
allowed only after a video review.  The Capitals lead the best-of-seven first-round series 1-0.
Game 2 is April 15 in Washington, and the series then moves to
